      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tariffs act as a protectionist tool that can shield domestic industries from foreign competition by raising the cost of imported goods. However, this often leads to higher prices for consumers and can provoke retaliatory measures from trading partners, potentially harming export-dependent businesses. Ultimately whether they are \"good\" depends on your economic perspective, as they offer short-term shelter for specific sectors but generally result in a net loss of economic efficiency for the economy as a whole.",
